This paper deals with computer vision tasks related to image and video saliency modeling, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel network architecture and domain adaptation techniques, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Gaussian priors and RNNs, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) research.
